<br>
Damage mitigation:  Warriors should be on thier own dmg mitigation table, which is superior to pal/sk.  As far as undead, I don't really think that should affect mitigation, but certainly dps.  If at any time hybrids took less damage from mob_001 then warriors would have nothing to do but stand there hoping the CH chain doesn't break.  Warriors should tank better than any other class, all the time...period.  <br>
<br>
Aggro:  It's really fukkered.  All I have to do is cast a lvl 9 spell and a lvl 15 spell, and my job is pretty much done.  No matter how crappy my equipment may be.  Hell, I could probably outaggro the typical warrior, without ever hitting attack.  In normal xp groups, without high-end proccing weaps, warriors are quite often chasing mobs down, while thier casters are getting whacked.  Doesn't make much sense, and warriors dont have many options, but to lower thier dps to get proccing weaps.  (This is excluding the top 5% of warrior 1handers).  Either make taunt a hell of a lot more effective, or give warriors something unique.  I don't know many people who wouldn't rather have a knight as thier xp tank.<br>
<br>
Disciplines:   I'm expecting hybrids to flame me for this, but I don't think we should get any sort of mitigation discipline.  Holyforge (undead crits) and Sanctification (situational spell immunity), while rather useless, make sense, but pure melee should rule this department.  Disciplines should be on different time tables as well.  Like someone said on the PoN boards lately, warriors rarely use any of thier offensive desciplines due to the fact that they have long refresh times, and they just might need one of thier defensive discs.  It's the same way with our LoH, noone's going to use it as a heal, just because it's up...it's an oh @#%$ sorta thing.<br>
Summary:  Unlike most paladins (from what I read on PoN)  I'm perfectly happy with my character, and the experiences I have.  Do I wish I had a strong raid role?  of course.  Do I wish I could BS, MB, FD, and CH?  sure.  But I've got a hell of a lot more options than alot of classes, warriors especially.  <br>
I apologize if this topic has already been beaten into the ground, but I hate it when paladins whine. <p><font size = 4 color = cyan> Darkgecko Notgeico<BR> <font size = 2 color = black> 55 Knight of Karana<BR>Spawn of Veeshan<BR>Bristlebane Server<BR> <font size = 2 color = blue> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=396867">My Equipment</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubalidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balidin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/18/02 7:09:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1430.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://saedyan.freeservers.com/images/pstgif.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tank balanceing from a old outdated paladin. What do u t</span><hr size=1> Let me get this straight, Warriors:<br>
