<br>
Paladins are not in a situation where they can never tank anything though, are they?  In fact, along with Shadow Knights, they are in fact the second best tank class in the game now?  Can you refute that?<br>
<br>
And can you refute that with stun it is possible for a Paladin to hold agro pretty securely, even with the recent stun changes?  Can you say in all truth and honesty (remember, you're a Paladin) that Paladins do not hold agro better than Warriors in those situations where stun does work?<br>
<br>
This is the real, valid comparison.  Warriors tank slightly better than Paladins, true.  Paladins hold agro slightly better than Warriors (some would argue significantly better, but recent stun changes make that debateable), true.  Warriors have slightly higher DPS than Paladins (somewhere between 5% to 20% better depending on a lot of variables), true.  Paladins have buffs and heals and some additional utility spells (root and flash of light do have their uses) that Warriors don't, true.<br>
<br>
What I see is two areas where Warriors have an edge over Paladins.  Damage absorptions (tanking) and damage dealing (DPS). <br>
<br>
I also see two areas where Paladins have an edge over Warriors.  Agro control (stuns)  and heals/buffs/spell utility.<br>
<br>
Asking Warriors to give up one of their areas of superiority in certain circumstances while not losing one of your areas of superiority in return is unreasonable.  Asking for additional upgrades and areas of superiority in addition borders on the asinine. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uvaraho1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Varaho1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 927<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/18/02 7:41:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1430.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tank balanceing from a old outdated paladin. What do u t</span><hr size=1> Do you know why? Because several paladins do not want balance, they wish to be overpowered. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukrazrussian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KrazRussian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/18/02 7:46:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1430.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tank balanceing from a old outdated paladin. What do u t</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;You want Paladins to unconditionally tank worse than you, and scream bloody murder when they ask for upgrades in DPS or anything else for that matter. What would a Paladin's role be then, if they could never tank anything? They gave up their offensive abilities for tanking abilities and defensive buffs, and you say that should mean nothing? &quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes. Basically. If you are still living in this notion that a paladin's only role is to tank, you sir are a moron. Let me explain something to paladins that keep trolling these boards screaming to have their raid role be defined as tanking:<br>
<br>
Hybrids are a class based on VERSATILITY. Versatility = no defined roles. What's a beastlord's role on a raid? A ranger's? Necro? Shadowknight? Paladin? Druids for that matter? Shaman on certain raids? <br>
<br>
Why do those classes not have defined raid roles? Because they are multi-purpose, they are &quot;renaissance&quot; classes. Each class can fulfill multiple purposes on a raid, and therefore are not restricted to any specific role. This is actually better in my opinion than having a very specific role on a raid. Example, if you have a raid with enough warriors tanking (which could actually mean only 1 or 2 warriors); the other warriors are basically dead weight with ensurance. If you have a raid with enough chanters to haste/kei; enchanters are basically dead weight.<br>
<br>
As to what roles paladins specifically hold on raids. Let me explain then:<br>
<br>
- If you don't believe in the effectiveness of paladin healing, then you've never fought a real AoE mob. If you have, you'd know that the two classes who make AoE raids (besides tank/cleric rotation that is) are Paladins (Wave of Prexuss) and SHamans (torpor). Understand this very clearly.<br>
- If you want further proof; if you've never fought a mob who hits for massive damage, with low delay and flurries, then you don't know the usefulness of paladin LoH. make no mistake; LoH is detremental when a tank first engages such a mob, when the rotation hasn't hit him yet.<br>
- If you don't believe in paladin DPS, then you have never been on a raid with a good paladin. Good paladins parse out sick damage; plain and simple. <br>
- If you don't believe paladins tank well, see above.<br>
<br>
Bottom line, your versatility more than compensates for your lack of being the best raid tank. It did before the HP % and damage % difference between warriors and knight was decreased. You damn well better believe it more than compensates for 700hp  and disc defensive, along with approximately 5% more damage output. <br>
<br>
P.S.; warriors want to get rid of /disc defensive only if we are put on separate damage mitigation tables where we mitigate about 15-20% better than any other classes. Otherwise, what are we but knight without the versatility and ability to gank agro, with 700 more HP. <p><center><p><font size = 3 colo = "blue"><b>Wilhelmm D'Averam<br>Warlord of the Apocalypse</b></font></p></center>

